Installing pyspex
=================

Download
--------
The latest release of pyspex is available from:

    https://github.com/rmvanhees/pyspex.git

Requires
--------
These external packages are required to install pyspex.

**HDF5 library** 1.10.5+ (https://portal.hdfgroup.org/display/support/Downloads)

**netCDF4 C-library** 4.7.4 (https://github.com/Unidata/netcdf-c)

**Python** 3.7 or later (https://www.python.org/)

**numpy** 1.17 or later (http://www.numpy.org/)

**h5py** 2.10  or later (https://www.h5py.org/)

**netCDF4** 1.5 or later (http://unidata.github.io/netcdf4-python/netCDF4)

**pys5p** 1.1 or later (https://github.com/rmvanhees/pys5p.git)

**pytiff** 0.8 or later (https://github.com/FZJ-INM1-BDA/pytiff)

**setuptools-scm** 3.0 or later (https://github.com/pypa/setuptools_scm/)

It is adviced to use 'pip3' to install the Python packages and to use the
latest versions of the software libraries.

You can easily verify if the packages are installed:

> pip3 list

Any missing package can be installed using:

> pip3 install <package-name>
or
> pip3 install <package-name> --user

The installation of pytiff requires libtiff5-dev

> sudo apt-get install libtiff5-dev


Install
-------
Once you have satisfied the requirements detailed below, simply run:

> python3 setup.py install           # as administrator
or
> python3 setup.py install --user    # as user
